Tools for denoising multichannel electrophysiological data (EEG, MEG, etc.)

Copyright 2007/2008 Alain de Cheveigne, Laboratoire de Psychologie de la Perception, 
CNRS and Universite Paris Descartes, and Departement d'Etudes Cognitives, Ecole 
Normale Superieure, Paris.  This software is provided as-is with no warranty.  
This software is provided for SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH purposes only.  If you use the 
tools (or the algorithms, or the ideas) in your research, you must cite the 
references below in all publications derived from this research.  If you wish to use 
these tools (or the algorithms, or the ideas) in a product, you must contact 
Alain.de.Cheveigne AT ens.fr for permission and/or licensing details.

The tools implement three basic denoising methods: TSPCA, SNS, and DSS-based spatial filtering. 
Cite as:
de Cheveign\'e, A. and Simon, J. Z. (2007). "Denoising based on Time-Shift PCA." Journal of Neuroscience Methods 165: 297-305.
de Cheveign\'e, A. and Simon, J. Z. (2007). "Sensor Noise Suppression." Journal of Neuroscience Methods 168: 195-202.
de Cheveigné, A. and Simon, J. Z. (2008). "Denoising based on spatial filtering." Journal of Neuroscience Methods 171: 331-339.

Look at the example files for hints to how to use these routines. 

